Data considerations:

  • 20 random ACP samples from each diagnosis were used, for the sake of computing power.
    • MS: ['AC002498', 'AC003028', 'AC002912', 'AC001158', 'AC002120', 'AC002041', 'AC001850', 'AC002814', 'AC001477', 'AC002949', 'AC000914', 'AC000872', 'AC002631', 'AC002355', 'AC001307', 'AC002241', 'AC002369', 'AC001835', 'AC000174', 'AC001629']
    • CTRL: ['AC000997', 'AC000362', 'AC001376', 'AC000577', 'AC000817', 'AC000860', 'AC000282', 'AC002238', 'AC000387', 'AC000979', 'AC003134', 'AC001836', 'AC000691', 'AC000148', 'AC002946', 'AC002217', 'AC001827', 'AC001755', 'AC000711', 'AC003255']
  • The processing pipeline was the following:
    • Cut x-axis [500,2600]
    • rp.preprocessing.baseline.IASLS(diff_order=3),
    • rp.preprocessing.normalise.MinMax()
  • The plots show the average and std deviation between all samples, 3 replicates (r) and 3 points (p).
